1. Import solr.war file from apache-solr.zip

2. Add solr.xml to the Eclipse Servers config directory and configure the paths.
Example:

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Context docBase="/Users/AppleCan/Desktop/Intranda/viewer/apache-solr/solr.war" crossContext="true">
  <Environment name="solr/home" type="java.lang.String" value="/Users/AppleCan/Desktop/Intranda/viewer/apache-solr" override="true"/>
</Context>

3. Configure the <env-entry /> in the web.xml of the solr directory to the local path of the solr.
The apache-solr directory inside the viewer works. It resides the config files.

4. Copy the corresponding index and media folder.
I try it out in the moment.

